    <h3>Record 2022 performance</h3>
    <p>
      Citgo&rsquo;s 2022 results reflected the extraordinary refining environment
      following Russia&rsquo;s invasion of Ukraine, which sent global crack spreads to
      historic highs. Citgo&rsquo;s complex refining system&mdash;designed to process
      discounted heavy crude into high-value light products&mdash;benefited
      disproportionately, generating an estimated $4.3&nbsp;billion in net income on
      $38.4&nbsp;billion in revenue. These profits accumulated within Citgo because
      sanctions prevented dividend repatriation to PDVSA.
