      stock exchange. There is no &ldquo;Citgo stock&rdquo; available for purchase.
      The company is a wholly owned indirect subsidiary of PDVSA, which is itself
      100% owned by the Venezuelan state. Citgo has never conducted an initial public
      offering (IPO), and there are no current plans for one.
    </p>
    <p>
      The only way Citgo ownership could change is through: (a) the Delaware court
      proceedings currently underway (the Elliott auction), (b) a government-to-government
      negotiated sale, or (c) a restructuring of PDVSA&rsquo;s obligations that
      preserves state ownership. For investors interested in exposure to Citgo&rsquo;s
      refining operations, the PDVSA&nbsp;2020 bonds trade in secondary markets at
      deep discounts, though these instruments carry extreme legal and credit risk.
    </p>
