        </button>
        <div class="faq-a">
          <p>
            No. Citgo is not a publicly traded company and has no stock listed on any
            exchange. It is a wholly owned subsidiary of the Venezuelan state oil company
            PDVSA. There is no &ldquo;Citgo stock ticker&rdquo; or way to buy shares.
            For investors seeking indirect exposure, PDVSA 2020 bonds trade in secondary
            markets at significant discounts, but these instruments carry extreme credit,
